Here’s the revised Buyer Details section with the legal reference “hereinafter referred to as the Buyer, which expression shall mean and include...” for clarity and legal validity:


---

8. BUYER DETAILS

The Buyer of the property is:

Name: [Buyer’s Full Name]

Age: [XX] Years

Father’s / Spouse’s Name: [Father’s or Spouse’s Name]

Permanent Address: [Full Permanent Address as per ID Proof]

Correspondence Address: [Current Address (if different from permanent address)]

Aadhaar No. (Optional): [XXXX-XXXX-XXXX]

PAN No.: [XXXXXXXXXX]

Email ID: [Buyer’s Email]

Mobile Number: [Buyer’s Contact Number]


(Hereinafter referred to as the “Buyer,” which expression shall mean and include his/her heirs, legal representatives, executors, administrators, successors, and permitted assigns, unless repugnant to the context or meaning thereof.)

Signature of Buyer:

[Buyer’s Name]
(Signature)
Date: [DD/MM/YYYY]


---

Why Include This Clause?

Ensures that the term "Buyer" includes their legal heirs, successors, and assigns.

Adds legal clarity in case of future property ownership transfer.

Protects the rights of the Buyer’s successors in unforeseen circumstances.


Would you like any additional legal clauses or modifications?

